TASK: Fix the forkpty() deadlock in vendor/tvterm/source/tvterm-core/pty.cc

PROBLEM:
When our TUI app calls forkpty() on the main thread AFTER background threads are
already running (from Scramble async popen calls), forkpty() deadlocks because
fork() in a multithreaded process can hang on internal libc/runtime locks held
by other threads.

THE FIX:
Replace forkpty() with openpty() + posix_spawn() (or manual fork+exec with
proper atfork safety) in vendor/tvterm/source/tvterm-core/pty.cc.

The current code at pty.cc:30-60 does:
  1. forkpty(&masterFd, nullptr, &termios, &winsize)  -- BLOCKS
  2. In child: setenv, signal setup, execvp(SHELL)
  3. In parent: set ptyDescriptor fields

Replace with:
  1. openpty(&masterFd, &slaveFd, nullptr, &termios, &winsize)
  2. posix_spawn() with file_actions to dup2 slaveFd to stdin/stdout/stderr
     and posix_spawnattr for setsid + signal defaults
  3. Close slaveFd in parent
  4. Set ptyDescriptor fields as before

IMPORTANT CONSTRAINTS:
- Must work on macOS (arm64) and Linux
- The child process needs: setsid(), controlling terminal setup, SHELL env exec
- posix_spawn on macOS doesnt support setsid directly in spawnattr --
  if needed, use a small intermediate approach: vfork()+exec or pipe-based
  synchronization. But try posix_spawn first.
- Keep the existing error handling (onError callback)
- Keep the debug fprintf to stderr in child on exec failure
- The custom environment vars must still be set in the child
- Include headers: <pty.h> or <util.h> (macOS), <spawn.h>, <fcntl.h>
- On macOS, openpty is in <util.h>; on Linux its in <pty.h>
- The existing code has '#if _WIN32' guards -- only change the Unix path

Also check: does the file already have platform ifdefs? Respect them.

Build test: cd build && make -j8 test_pattern
The build must succeed.

Write the fix, build it, and report what you changed.
